---
import Heading from "../components/ui/Heading.astro"
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Mum's Memories - Now"
  description="Progress updates on Mum's Memories, my baby journaling app."
>

  <Heading level="h2" as="h1" class="mt-6 mb-8">
    Mum's Memories
    <a
      href="https://mumsmemories.app"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="text-muted-foreground/60 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors no-underline ml-1.5 inline-flex items-center align-middle"
      aria-label="Mum's Memories website"
    >
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/></svg>
    </a>
  </Heading>

  <div class="space-y-10">
    <section>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-3">Summary</Heading>
      <p>
        Mum's Memories is a minimal baby journaling app I am building for my own use.
        Parents can record milestones and write letters to their baby.
        I am getting it ready for a wider release.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-4">Updates</Heading>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <time
            datetime="2026-07-08"
            class="text-sm font-medium text-heading tracking-wide uppercase mb-3 block"
          >
            July 8, 2026
          </time>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Simplified the data model. I collapsed entry types down to just note
                and milestone. I felt that early types were mostly redundant.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Merged Timeline and Memories into a single Journal tab with Day and
                Browse views. This is still a work in progress. I think with more
                features in the future, I may bring back the navbar tabs.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Cut onboarding down to 5 screens. Completely removed the premium
                upsell screens. Now, onboarding can be finished in under 90 seconds.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Set up a staging Docker Compose stack and wired EAS build profiles
                to it. Still need to set up staging R2 bucket and domains, but this
                is a good start. It will let me test new features in a
                production-like environment before releasing.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Personalised the writing prompts in the composer screen. They now
                adapt to the baby name and age. Still no AI, but the prompts feel
                personal now.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Added milestone age-at-date stamps and a Firsts index in Browse. It
                is now easy to see all the firsts of the baby in one place.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span
                class="mt-2.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted-foreground/40"
              ></span>
              <span>
                Changed the architecture from per-baby profiles to a blended view
                throughout the app. It is easy to filter by baby, and the default
                view shows all babies together. This was a big change, but I think it
                is the right one.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
